class Solution {
    public int canBeTypedWords(String text, String brokenLetters) {

        String parts[] =  text.split("\\s+");
        int cnt = 0;
        
        for(String word : parts){
            boolean cantype = true;

            for(char broken : brokenLetters.toCharArray()){
                if(word.indexOf(broken) != -1){
                    cantype = false;
                    break;
                }
            }
            if(cantype){
                cnt++;;
            }
        }

        return cnt;

    }
}

There is a malfunctioning keyboard where some letter keys do not work. All other keys on the keyboard work properly.
Given a string text of words separated by a single space (no leading or trailing spaces) and a string brokenLetters of all distinct letter keys that are broken,
return the number of words in text you can fully type using this keyboard.

 

Example 1:

Input: text = "hello world", brokenLetters = "ad"
Output: 1
Explanation: We cannot type "world" because the 'd' key is broken.

indexOf is used to detect if a  letter exists in the word or not .

T.C => O(N)
S.C = O(1)
